  "text": "The Grafana dashboard JSON schema version migration pipeline is composed of backend (Go) and frontend (TypeScript) components that work in tandem to migrate dashboard definitions from older schema versions to the latest version (42).\n\n## Backend Migration Runner and Registry\n\nThe **migration runner** is implemented in `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/migrate.go`. This file contains the `Migrate()` function which is the primary entry point that orchestrates the entire migration process. The `Initialize()` function sets up the migrator singleton with required dependencies. The core migration logic processes dashboards through the following steps:\n1. Cleans up backend-only properties (`__elements`, `__inputs`, `__requires`)\n2. Tracks original transformations and field configurations\n3. Applies frontend defaults to match DashboardModel and PanelModel constructors\n4. Ensures panels have unique IDs\n5. Executes the versioned migration chain (v2 through v42)\n6. Adds built-in annotation queries\n7. Cleans up the dashboard for persistence\n\nThe **migration registry** is defined in `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/migrations.go`. The `GetMigrations()` function returns a map of `int` to `SchemaVersionMigrationFunc` that registers all 41 versioned migrations (versions 2-42). The schema version constants `MIN_VERSION` (0) and `LATEST_VERSION` (42) define the supported migration range. This file also defines the `SchemaVersionMigrationFunc` type as `func(context.Context, map[string]interface{}) error` and the `GetSchemaVersion()` utility function that safely extracts the schema version from dashboard JSON.\n\n## Individual Migration Steps\n\nEach schema version migration is implemented as a separate function in dedicated files:\n- `V2` (v2.go): Migrates legacy services.filter structure to dashboard.time and templating.list\n- `V3` (v3.go) through `V42` (v42.go): Each implements specific schema transformations\n- `V33` and `V36` are special: they are higher-order functions that take a `DataSourceInfoProvider` parameter, enabling context-aware migrations for datasource resolution\n\nFor example, `V36` migrates dashboard datasource references from legacy string names to structured UID-based objects, handling:\n- Annotation datasource conversions\n- Template variable datasource migrations  \n- Panel and target-level datasource references\n- Default datasource resolution\n- Special datasources like Mixed (`__mixed__`) and Expressions (`__expr__`)\n\n## Supporting Utilities\n\nSeveral utility files support the migration pipeline:\n- `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/migration_utils.go`: Common utility functions like `GetStringValue()`, `GetBoolValue()`, `GetIntValue()`, `GetFloatValue()` for safe type conversions\n- `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/datasource_utils.go`: Datasource-specific migration helpers for datasource name/ref conversions\n- `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/errors.go`: Custom error types `MigrationError` and `MinimumVersionError` for detailed error reporting\n- `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/frontend_defaults.go`: Applies DashboardModel constructor defaults (title, tags, timezone, time range, etc.) to match frontend behavior\n- `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/metrics.go`: Metrics collection for migration telemetry\n\n## Frontend TypeScript Migrator\n\nThe **frontend DashboardMigrator** is implemented in `public/app/features/dashboard/state/DashboardMigrator.ts`. This TypeScript class mirrors the backend migration logic and is the primary entry point for dashboard migrations on the frontend. Key features:\n\n- `DASHBOARD_SCHEMA_VERSION` constant set to 42 (marked as final version for v1 dashboard API)\n- `updateSchema()` method orchestrates all panel-level and dashboard-level migrations\n- Migration blocks for versions 2-42 that handle:\n  - Variable and annotation migrations (v2, v6, v12, v23, v27-29)\n  - Panel type migrations (v4, v8-10, v13, v18, v22, v24, v26, v30, v33-34, v37-39, v42)\n  - Grid layout upgrades (v16)\n  - Datasource name-to-ref conversions (v33, v36)\n  - CloudWatch query migrations (v34)\n  - Table cell display format migrations (v38)\n  - Legend and tooltip option migrations (v30, v37)\n  - Transform configuration migrations (v31, v39)\n\n- Supporting methods:\n  - `upgradeToGridLayout()`: Converts legacy row-based layouts to grid-based layouts\n  - `migrateCloudWatchQueries()`: Migrates CloudWatch-specific query formats\n  - `migrateCloudWatchAnnotationQuery()`: Splits CloudWatch annotation queries with multiple statistics\n  - Helper functions for value mappings, tooltip options, x-axis visibility, and hideFrom functionality\n\nThe frontend migrator uses panel upgrade handlers (stored in `panelUpgrades` array) that are applied to all panels (including nested panels in row panels) to ensure consistent migration behavior across the entire dashboard structure.\n\n## Migration Pipeline Architecture\n\nThe complete migration chain works as follows:\n\n1. **Frontend invokes migration**: `DashboardMigrator.updateSchema()` is called with the loaded dashboard JSON\n2. **Backend initialization**: `Initialize()` registers all migrations via `GetMigrations()`\n3. **Version detection**: `GetSchemaVersion()` determines the current schema version\n4. **Sequential versioning**: For each version from current+1 to target version, the corresponding migration function is executed\n5. **Type conversions**: Migrations handle Go/TypeScript type compatibility (float64 vs int for schema version)\n6. **Error handling**: Custom error types provide detailed failure information with version context\n7. **Persistence**: Final dashboard is cleaned to match frontend `getSaveModel()` behavior\n\nBoth backend and frontend implementations maintain feature parity for dashboard migrations, with the backend handling Kubernetes-style API conversions (v0alpha1, v1beta1, v2alpha1, v2beta1) for dashboard resources alongside the JSON schema versio